    <summary>Synchronizes qBittorrent's listening port with the port assigned by your VPN provider</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## qbPortWeaver

qbPortWeaver is a lightweight Windows system tray application that automatically synchronizes the listening port of [qBittorrent](https://www.qbittorrent.org/) with the port assigned by your VPN provider.

### Supported VPN Providers

- **ProtonVPN** — reads the forwarded port via the ProtonVPN local API
- **Private Internet Access (PIA)** — reads the forwarded port from the PIA port-forwarding payload file

### Features

- Runs silently in the Windows system tray
- Automatically detects VPN port changes and updates qBittorrent via its Web API
- Optional Windows startup integration
- Built-in automatic update checker
- Supports a custom post-update PowerShell command (e.g., send an email notification)
- File-based logging with automatic rotation
- JSON status file for external monitoring

### Requirements

- Windows 10/11 (x64)
- qBittorrent with Web UI enabled
- ProtonVPN or Private Internet Access (PIA) with port forwarding enabled

### Configuration

On first launch, open **Settings** from the system tray icon to configure:
- qBittorrent Web UI URL and credentials
- VPN provider selection
- Sync interval
- Startup options
    ]]></description>
